c OC1CON = 0x0006; // PWM mode on OC1 PR2 = 39999; // Period for 1 kHz PWM OC1RS
                   // = 20000; // 50% duty cycle T2CON = 0x8000; // Timer2 ON,
                   // prescaler 1:1
```

To configure the PIC24 oscillator with a 3 MHz crystal and PLL for a 60 MHz system clock: 1. Set the FOSCSEL and FOSC configuration registers to enable the primary oscillator with PLL. Example: FOSCSEL = 0x0000; FOSC = 0x0001;. 2. Configure the PLL settings: PLLPRE = 0 (N1 = 2), PLLDIV = 78 (M = 80), PLLPOST = 0 (N2 = 2). 3. Write the main program to set the PLL registers and enable the oscillator. Example: ```
c void main(void) {
  PLLDIV = 78;
  PLLPRE = 0;
  PLLPOST = 0;
  builtin_write_OSCCONH(0x03);
  builtin_write_OSCCONL(0x01);
  while (OSCCONbits.OSWEN == 1)
    ;
}
```

To configure Timer1 for an RTC using a 32.768 kHz crystal: 1. Set the T1CON register to enable Timer1 with the secondary oscillator. Example: T1CON = 0x8002; // Timer1 ON, prescaler 1:1, secondary oscillator. 2. Set PR1 to 32767 for a 1-second interrupt period. 3. Enable the Timer1 interrupt by setting the T1IE bit in the IEC0 register. 4. Write the ISR to increment the timekeeping variables. Example: ```
c void __attribute__((interrupt, auto_psv)) _T1Interrupt(void) {
  seconds++;
  if (seconds == 60) {
    minutes++;
    seconds = 0;
  }
  IFS0bits.T1IF = 0;
}
```

To calculate the PLL settings for a 6 MHz crystal to achieve a 30 MHz system clock: 1. Choose N2 = 4 (PLLPOST = 1) to set Fvco = 120 MHz. 2. Calculate N1 and M: For N1 = 2, M = 120 MHz / 3 MHz = 40. 3. Set the PLL registers: PLLPRE = 0 (N1 = 2), PLLDIV = 38 (M = 40), PLLPOST = 1 (N2 = 4). Example: ```
c PLLDIV = 38;
PLLPRE = 0;
